  "market_context": "After a strong hourly downtrend (26020→25220), price consolidated internally. At ~09:30 NY open, a bearish reversal setup formed with expansion lower expected. Analyst focused on 15-min change in state of delivery and 1-min protected swing for entry.",
  "key_observation": "The hourly candle 3 closure formed a bearish reversal candle with a large lower wick; the 15-min chart showed a clear change in state of delivery confirming bearish bias, enabling a 1-min continuation entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify hourly candle 3 as an expansion candle with a bearish reversal structure (large lower wick) indicating potential downside continuation.",
    "Step 2: Drop to 15-minute timeframe to confirm change in state of delivery (CISD) — price closed below prior down-close candles, validating bearish shift.",
    "Step 3: Locate the protected swing on the 1-minute chart at the end of the 15-min CISD candle, marking it as the stop-loss level.",
    "Step 4: Enter short on 1-minute continuation candle after the protected swing formed, targeting 2R or the consolidation low.",
    "Step 5: Confirm alignment: hourly bias (expansion down), 15-min CISD, and 1-min protected swing all pointing bearish."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target successfully.",
  "lessons": "Advanced reversal scalping requires precise multi-timeframe alignment: hourly reversal candle must be confirmed by 15-min CISD and 1-min protected swing. Only trade when all three timeframes concur; otherwise, wait for cleaner setups.",
